{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place almonds in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a large bowl.","Place celery, onions and dill in mixing bowl then chop <b>2 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Add chickpeas and chop <b>1 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to bowl with almonds.","Place avocado, lemon juice, nutritional yeast, garlic powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Transfer to bowl with chickpea mixture then stir well with spatula to combine. Serve immediately in sandwiches, or cover with cling film and store in fridge for up to 3 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g blanched almonds","100 g celery stalks, cut in 3 pieces","80 g red onions, quartered","5 g fresh dill leaves","480 g cooked chickpeas, rinsed, drained (2 x 400 g tins)","1 ripe avocado, cut in pieces (3 cm)","80 g lemon juice (approx. 2 lemons)","1 Tbsp nutritional yeast flakes","2 tsp garlic powder","2 tsp smoked paprika","2 pinches cayenne pepper","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r300148","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-zeqXtz1QA4c\/XZaql-54dXI\/AAAAAAAAheg\/i6klpIcyJbAZanLTaDrVSuXykjiYzxWFgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_fZPMacWuKN8WD3z2.png","title":"Vegan Chickpea and Almond Sandwich Filling","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"71 g","fat":"99 g","uom":"per 1 Total recipe","carbohydrates":"95 g","calories":"6888 kJ \/ 1655 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, large bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["While sometimes only a sandwich will do, it’s easy to get stuck in a rut of eating the same fillings. This creative, meat-free version uses roughly chopped chickpeas, crunchy almonds and red onion all held together in a smoky paprika dressing. Using creamy avocado instead of mayonnaise also makes it suitable for vegans.","Delicious served with the <i>Mini Everything Bagels<\/i>."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","15m","1"]}